The paper deals with complexity measures in communication complexity and pseudorandomness, which are typically studied in the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of decision trees and composition theorems suggests that the paper may also be relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The study of lower bounds on specific functions such as $\mathsf{Sort}$ and $\mathsf{HI}$ may fall under the sub-categories of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and machine learning (cs.LG).
